Iceland(Island) 
Since this location points towards Reykjavik which is the capital city of Island Country. As we know it is also one of largest Capital area and also known for large number of cars per capita. So when people get there own car after getting license at age of 17 , most probably they donot use public transportation and so taxi service is very expensive too comparing other places of similar size and nature like cities in US. Also because Islanders live far away from main continent in terms of kilometers, costal line and climate has significant effect on culture, art and lifestyle of locals living there since years ago even before Christ era. Thus this place can be considered worth visiting if someone wants to experience something unique with less tourist crowds compared to places like Paris, Barcelona, Rome, Athens etc.
Regards,
Cartographer.

Canada (Canadian French: [kanada])[a] is a country located in North America. Its ten provinces and three territories extend from the Atlantic Ocean to the Pacific Ocean and northward into the Arctic Ocean, making it the world's second largest country by total area.[d] It has the world's longest coastline and is famed for its natural beauty, wildlife, and national and provincial parks. Canada is also renowned for its cold winter temperatures,[b][c] which however have been moderating over recent decades due to global warming.[d][8][e]

Indigenous peoples have continuously inhabited what is now Canada since prehistory, beginning at least 15,000 years ago during the last glacial period when people first crossed regions now covered by ice into what is now Alaska.[f] In the late 16th century, British and French expeditions explored and later settled along the Atlantic coast.[g] As many as half of all Canadians claim either full or partial descent from immigrants who came following the United Empire Loyalist exodus after the American Revolutionary War.[h] To gain more settlers, Canada began offering free land grants for farmers to settle Western Canada during the 1880s and 1890s; this was especially true about the Canadian Prairies which attracted hundreds of thousands of homesteaders to what is today the provinces of Alberta, Saskatchewan, and Manitoba. data.sampled:
Pakistan(Urdu: پاکستان)
Pakistan is an Islamic republic located in South Asia. It has a coastline along the Arabian Sea and Gulf of Oman in the south. To the north it borders Afghanistan and Iran, while India is located to the east. China bounds its northern and western edges while Kashmir lies to the northeast. A narrow strip of land known as the Wagah Attari border connects the easternmost part of the country to India. Westwards from there, Pakistan shares an ocean boundary with Somalia which stretches out over thousands of miles. Most recently added Pishin district of Balochistan province share short Land Border with United Arab Emirates. 

Gilgit–Baltistan formerly known as Northern Areas  & Azad Jammu and Kashmirare also regions in Pakistan that lie on either side of Line of Control i.e LOC. These regions have special constitutional status within the country. Gilgit Baltistan was established as a single administrative unit in 1970, comprising territory on both sides of the Karakoram Highway which runs through it. Skardu is largest city in Gilgit Baltistan by population.
The capital of Pakistan is Islamabad and Largest City is Karachi . Other major cities include , Lahore, Faisalabad, Rawalpindi, Hyderabad, Multan, Peshawar, Quetta and Sialkot. The country's population reached the milestone of 220 million people earlier this year .
Although Urdu is national Language but English is also widely spoken across the Country especially when it comes to Higher Education and Corporate sector. Pashto , Punjabi , Sindhi and Balochi are other Regional languages spoken in various parts of the country .
